### Links to fill in

Every demo page has placeholder links marked `href="#"` or `(link TBD)` in the Red Hat section. Before launch, replace these with:

- Red Hat AI product documentation URLs
- Relevant Red Hat blog posts
- Any internal landing pages or product pages

Search for `link TBD` across all HTML files to find them all.

### Demo 06 (GuideLLM)

Tile 06 currently links to `#`. The plan is a live benchmarking visualization pulling from pre-run GuideLLM results across a set of models. Reach out to [fill in owner] to coordinate data format and hosting.

### Content accuracy

Stats in the hero (`6×`, `−70%`, `100%`) and benchmark numbers in the sparsification demo (MMLU, HumanEval, GSM8K degradation curves) are approximate and illustrative. If this site gets used in formal customer-facing materials, have an engineer review the numbers against current benchmarks.

### Fonts and branding

The demos use Red Hat's official font family (Red Hat Display, Text, Mono) which is open source and available via Google Fonts — no license issues for external hosting. The hat SVG in the header is a simplified geometric approximation, not the official Red Hat logo. Replace with the official SVG asset if needed for brand compliance.

### Contributing

PRs welcome. New demos should follow the same layout patterns (`DemoNav`, explainer + Red Hat + upstream sections) and reuse shared styles in `src/styles/` so the suite stays visually coherent.

